localString.value: While Goblins are often considered little more than a nuisance, an unchecked population can often balloon into a serious threat to normally civilized areas.
This amulet will allow the user to call forth a magical oxen from the Astral plane. While such a beast cannot fight, it can carry a very heavy load with no effort at all.
This is your basic copper fletching knife used in fletching.
This is your basic copper paring knife used in bowyering.
Essence of Acid for making Acid Arrows and Bolts.
Essence of Electricity for making Electrical Arrows and Bolts.
Essence of Fire for making Flaming Arrows and Bolts.
Essence of Cold for making Frozen Arrows and Bolts.
Pulley for making compound bows. Note that you will need two for each bow; one for each end of the bow.
Hemp Cord is the basic bow string.
Pumice Stone is used to smooth out wood products to a fine finish.
Silk Cord is a medium-strength bow string.

For the advanced bower or fletcher, there are extra tools and supplies that may be used.
A pumice is needed to create a smooth bow. You can purchase a Large Pumice Stone which can be broken up into 10 smaller pieces which are ideal for crafting.
A skilled tanner may make a waxed leather cord that is needed for some bows...he can do this with a tanned small hide, some beeswax and his sewing kit. If no tanner is available, this cord is often for sale.
Magical essence potions can be used by a fletcher to create enchanted ammunition. It may be possible to brew these potions using harvested components from creatures and other sources.
This large pumice stone must be broken up into smaller pieces to be used in Bowyering.
Waxed Leather Cord is the strongest bow string and is used for compound bows.
Advanced Arrow Head. Designed for advanced arrows that require some type of essence.
This is an oil flask. You may use it to refill a lantern, or try to light it and throw at someone
A flask of acid that can be thrown at enemies.
Alchemist's Fire is a sticky, adhesive substance that ignites on contact with air.
Used as often in the peasant's home as the dungeon's dark, these simple concoctions are common throughout Faerun.
These curative potions are too expensive for most civilians, and are used almost exclusively by soldiers and adventurers.
This is the primary tool thieves use to disarm traps and pick locks
Place this object in any area where you want tracking to occur. Set Will to the DC of tracking in this area.
The weapons lean into the wooden rack, waiting for release.
This is a fletchers desk used for making arrows.
